  "texts": [
    "Note that the best and second-best performances are highlighted only within the IID, Mild, Medium, and Extreme scenarios since we aim to investigate the impact of different data heterogeneity.",
    "We find that fine-tuning LLMs with heterogeneous code can still enhance the repairing capability and achieve promising results.",
    "compared to the IID distribution.",
    "In Table 5, we see that both CodeLlama-13B and CodeLlama-7B are slightly influenced by fine-tuning under some of the heterogeneous code complexity scenarios.",
    "There is a maximal decrease of only 3.68% on 𝑇𝑜𝑝@5 while fine-tuning CodeLlama-13B under the extreme Non-IID scenario and a reduction of 6.75% on 𝑇𝑜𝑝@10 while fine-tuning CodeLlama-7B with mild Non-IID distribution."
